<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-10-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 189.</note>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Brent to Mr. Fish</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 241.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United
                                        States,</hi><hi rend="italic"> Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-10-27"><hi rend="italic">Peru,
                                        October</hi> 27, 1870</date>. (Received November 28,
                                1870.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that on the
                            24th instant his ex cellency President Balta issued a proclamation
                            declaring the neutrality of Peru in the existing war between France and
                            Prussia.</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>